<div class="hgroup"><h1 class="title"><span class="title">Change the date and time</span></h1></div>
<div class="region">
<div class="contents">
<p class="p">If the date and time displayed on the menu bar are incorrect or in the wrong
 format, you can change them:</p>
<div class="steps"><div class="inner"><div class="region"><ol class="steps">
<li class="steps"><p class="p">To adjust the time and date, click on the clock located in the <span class="gui">menu bar</span>
and select <span class="gui">Date &amp; Time Settings</span>.</p></li>
<li class="steps"><p class="p">Change the system time zone by clicking on the map or entering your city into the <span class="gui">Location</span> box.</p></li>
<li class="steps"><p class="p">By default, Ubuntu periodically synchronizes the clock with a very accurate clock
on the Internet so you don't have to set your clock manually.</p></li>
</ol></div></div></div>
</div>
